cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper presents a learning method for sequence labeling tasks, which is a common problem in natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The method also involves learning multiple models and facilitating learning transfer through parameter sharing, which are common techniques in machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL). Therefore, the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper experiments with two applications, which could involve image or video analysis, leading to a possible category of cs.CV (Computer Vision).
